By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, March 30, 2023, closed with 18 or by Supplementary nomination of $4,000 at time of entry. $1,500 to enter and an additional $1,500 t o start with $200,000 guaranteed of which $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Graded Stake allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will b e presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELM DRIVE was off alertly from inside, chased then went up to press the pace from inside, dueled with LEGGS GALORE around the bend then vied inside a pair of rivals into the lane, drew clear in upper stretch remained strong to the wire under right-handed encouragement. BIG SUMMER stalked four wide into the turn, bid four deep at the quarter pole, gained command and led into the drive, was overtaken by ELM DRIVE in upper stretch, drifted in a bit in midstretch and held the place. KIRSTENBOSCH was off a bit slow to start, trailed three wide into the turn, angled over to the rail around the bend, steered out in upper stretch and rallied late for the show. AWAKE AT MIDNYTE stalked two wide into the turn, tipped out and bid three deep at the quarter pole, could not keep pace with ELM DRIVE in upper stretch, was bothered a by BIG SUMMER drifted inward midstretch and lost the show. CANOODLING forwardly placed off the inside up the backstretch, raced between rivals three wide into the turn, got crowded a bit at the three-eighths pole, chased three wide into the lane and weakened. FREEDOM FLYER broke a step slow from outside, chased widest up the backstretch, rounded the bend five wide and weakened. LEGGS GALORE showed early speed to take the front then set the pace outside ELM DRIVE, dueled with that rival around the turn, failed to keep up past the quarter pole, tired and eased in the furlong grounds and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Santa Anita Oaks - Grade2 SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 11 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 95. Stakes Purse 400000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLD FILLIES. By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, March 30, 2023, closed with 15 or by Supplementary nomination of $8,000 due at time of entry. $3,000 to enter and an additional $3,000 to start with $400,000 guarantee d of which $240,000 (PLUS ONE HUNDRED KENTUCKY OAKS POINTS) to the winner, $80,000 (Forty Ky. Oaks Points) to second, $48,000 (Thirty Ky. Oaks Points) to third, $24,000 (Twenty Ky. Oaks Points) to fourth and $8,000 (Ten Ky. Oaks Points) to fifth. 124 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAIZA broke well then took a stalking position outside a rival, gained up the backstretch and bid three deep into the far turn, dueled outside CLEARLY UNHINGED around the bend, took over at the quarter pole, shook free at the top of the lane and powered away under left-handed urging and was in-hand nearing the wire. AND TELL ME NOLIES chased three to four wide around the first turn, got bumped while three deep at the three-eighths pole, took aim three wide into the stretch but could not make any headway on the FAIZA and churned on to best the rest. WINDOW SHOPPING was off a bit slow, sat off the pace a bit off the rail early, had to check hard behind VENGANZA and altered out to bumped CLIQUISH nearing the three-eighths pole, entered the lane four wide and finished willingly for the show honors. CLEARLY UNHINGED broke a step slow, stalked two wide into the first turn, gained ground on the leader in the middle stages, launched a bid between rivals into the far turn, took over at the three-eighths pole, dueled with the winner around the bend and lost command at the quarter pole, could not keep up at the top of the stretch and weakened in the lane. VENGANZA was off slow in the beginning, chased from inside, took closer order up the backstretch, had to check and altered out when getting blocked behind GILA early on the far turn, chased two wide into the lane and weakened. DON'T GET PICKLED trailed four wide on the first turn, remained wide to the stretch and passed tired rivals. CLIQUISH broke a step slow, chased two wide into the first then had to steadied behind rival, chased between on the backstretch, got bumped hard and had to take up at the three-eighths pole and was not persevered with in the final furlong. GILA bobbled leaving the gate then sprinted clear and opened up around the first turn, held a diminishing lead nearing the far turn, was overtaken with three furlong remaining, tired around the far turn and had little left for the drive. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE INCIDENT ON THE FAR TURN AND FOLLOWING A REVIEW RULED THAT GILA CAUSED THE CHAIN REACTION BETWEEN SEVERAL RUNNERS AND SINCE SHE FINISHED LAST NO CHANGE WOULD BE MADE.

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANCIENT PEACE quickly cleared and went three wide around the clubhouse turn, opened up while staying off the inside up the backstretch, padded the lead inside to two wide on the far turn, continued far in front into the final furlong without ever being asked and was geared down late in an impressive victory. CHLOE'S CROWN broke out , tucked inside at the back, raced two wide into the far turn then found the rail again and finished willingly for a clear second. ACT OF SERENDIPITY chased a bit off the rail early, traveled along the fence on the far turn then two wide into the drive and lacked a bid. PRECIOUS BABY was off a bit slow in the beginning, chased five wide around the first turn, three wide around the far turn and weakened. ROSE BARTON (IRE) fractious in the gate, broke a step slow, chased four wide early, dropped back while remaining wide on the far turn, eased in the lane and walked off.
